Reading in the data¶

EDA is one of the important steps in builidng a machine learning model. It helps in feature selection and dimensionality reduction. Feature selection helps in deciding the candidate features in supervised or unsupervised machine learning models.

Using both training and testing data for EDA can lead to selecting bad models because we get low cross validation error which is not natural. So only Training data is used for exploratory data analysis becuase it gives good feature selection compared to the features selection when both training and testing data are used.

# Matplotlib defaults
def set_default_args():
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [6,4]
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 72
    plt.rcParams['axes.labelsize'] = 'medium'
    plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 'large'
    plt.xticks(fontsize=10)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=10)


def enlarge_image():
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [20,10]
    plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 200
    plt.rcParams['axes.labelsize'] = 25
    plt.rcParams['axes.titlesize'] = 25
    plt.xticks(fontsize=20)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=20)

# Function to calculate daysof the week
def weekday_count(start, end):
    start_date  = datetime.datetime.strptime(start, '%d/%m/%Y')
    end_date    = datetime.datetime.strptime(end, '%d/%m/%Y')
    week        = {}
    for i in range((end_date - start_date).days):
        day       = calendar.day_name[(start_date + datetime.timedelta(days=i+1)).weekday()]
        week[day] = week[day] + 1 if day in week else 1
    return week

count_dict = weekday_count("31/12/2015","30/06/2016")
print(count_dict)

{'Friday': 26, 'Saturday': 26, 'Sunday': 26, 'Monday': 26, 'Tuesday': 26, 'Wednesday': 26, 'Thursday': 26}

After completing the EDA over the temporal aspect and seeing through the trends of trip duration over months, day of the month, day of the week and hour of the day, we can select these four features as the candidate_feature for building the model.

Hence, the correlations between the candidate features must be checked and if they are correlated then one of the correlated features must be eliminated in the model building process

Finding the correlation between the candidate features¶

Candidate features are as follows:

  • month: Month of the year
  • hour: Hour of the day
  • day: day of the month
  • week: day of the week
